<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Silent Auction Coordinator / Development Associate</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Silent Auction Coordinator/Development Associate<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Nancy Kleve, Office Manager / Lisa Lane, Development<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: 50 &ndash; 100%, (20 to 40 hours per week) Exempt, 10 month position (Sept &ndash; June)</p>

<p><strong>Responsibilities/Roles</strong></p>
	  <p>1. Coordinate the PACER Benefit Silent Auction</p>
	<ul>
      <li>Act as coordinator for the Silent Auction Committee and collaborate with all silent auction volunteers</li>
      <li>Develop relationships with current volunteers and recruit new volunteers for the silent auction committee, building a team spirit</li>
      <li>Set meeting dates for Benefit and Silent Auction committees; coordinate the printing and distribution of notices, reminders, agendas, and meeting details</li>
      <li>Send correspondence to donors</li>
      <li>Generate ideas for new silent auction donations</li>
      <li>Make contacts with previous donors</li>
      <li>Solicit contributions from new donors</li>
      <li>Responsible for collecting donations: receiving donations and coordinating pick-up</li>
      <li>Track status of all donations, using a database system and other organizational systems</li>
      <li>Physically organize donated items with assistance from volunteers</li>
      <li>Review descriptions of all items</li>
      <li>Develop, coordinate and review content of silent auction catalog</li>
      <li>Develop table plan for items and floor plan for auction with assistance from PACER staff and volunteers</li>
      <li>Coordinate logistics of event day; including room set up and take down</li>
      <li>Follow through with collecting items, both on-site, or off-site</li>
    </ul>
    <p>2. Assist with benefit committees, including meetings and other activities</p>
    <p>3. Contribute information about program activities on website</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Work with web and graphic designers</li>
    <li>Review and contribute content to web based forms</li>
    </ul>
    <p>4. Participate in corporate sponsor cultivation</p>
    <p>5. Serve as part of corporate sponsorship team when needed</p>
    <p>6. Assist with special projects</p>
    <p>7. Other duties as required</p>
<p><strong>EXPERIENCE/BACKGROUND SKILLS</strong></p>
  <ol>
    <li>College degree or equivalent background gained through training or work experience</li>
    <li>Excellent communications skills and ability to relate to diverse groups</li>
    <li>Demonstrated ability to meet timelines and give attention to detail</li>
    <li>Ability to work collaboratively </li>
    <li>Excellent organizational skills</li>
    <li>Ability to keep good records and collect data for evaluation purposes</li>
    <li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>
    <li>Knowledge of/sensitivity to issues related to persons with disabilities</li>
    <li>Experience working with MicroSoft Word/Excel or interest in learning basic computer skills.</li>
  </ol>
<p><a name="OLE_LINK1" id="OLE_LINK1"><strong>SALARY</strong></a> :&nbsp; To be determined based on experience<br />
  Position available immediately.<br />
  Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
  Send resume with a letter of application to:<br />
  Human Resources | PACER Center | 8161 Normandale Blvd | Minneapolis, MN 55437</p>

